\fs34 Usage Overview.\

\fs24 ABKey is a plugin for Apple's Address Book that provides a friendly interface to the GnuPG key information for your Address Book Contacts. It provides summary and detailed key information for any Contact with one or more keys in your keychain (based on their email addresses) as well as allowing you to refresh key information and search for new keys on a Key Server.\
\
ABKey also integrates with recent versions of GPGMail (http://www.sente.ch/software/GPGMail/) \'d0 a GnuPG encryption plugin for Apple's Mail app. Together, ABKey and GPGMail allow you to specify signing and encryption preferences on a per-contact basis. You can now specifically always encrypt when emailing one particular contact while explicitly not encrypting or signing when emailing another contact \'d0 useful for email lists and contacts still using older versions of Outlook or Outlook Express.\
\
