\fs34 Setting per-contact GPGMail preferences\

\fs24 The ABKey plugin can co-operate with GPGMail (http://www.sente.ch/software/GPGMail/) to provide you with finer control over how GPGMail behaves when you send a Contact an email. This allows you to specify, for instance, that you always want to encrypt emails to a contact.\
\
By default, GPGMail preferences will appear for each contact \'d0 an example of which is shown below:\
\pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural
\cf0 \
