ABKey installs an additional preference pane for the Address Book which allows you to control how the plugin behaves. By default, ABKey will display all keys for a contact \'d0 including revoked, invalid, expired and disabled keys. You may turn off display of these keys by unchecking the relevant tick-box.\
\
You can control whether the GPGMail options fields display at the top of the card (below the title and key fields) or at the bottom of the card (just above the Notes field) using the drop-down menu.\
\
Checking the 'Keyserver Refresh buttons' will enable in-card refresh buttons per key. See Refreshing Key Information (below) for more information on this.\
\
Checking the 'Show card search button' field will allow you to search the Key Server for new keys for a Contact. See the chapter on searching for new keys (below) for more information on this.\
